SIMPLE: reprise
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reprise
<hw>Re*prise"</hw> <pr>(r?-pr?z")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>reprise</ets>, fr. <ets>reprendre</ets>, <ets>repris</ets>, to take
back, L. <ets>reprehendere</ets>. See <er>Reprehend</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A taking by way of retaliation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Deductions and
duties paid yearly out of a manor and lands, as rent charge, rent seck,
pensions, annuities, and the like.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>reprizes</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A ship recaptured from an enemy or from a
pirate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reprise</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Reprise
<hw>Re*prise"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>reprize</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take again; to
retake.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To recompense; to pay.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repristinate</ent>⟦br⟧
